{"type":"message","id":"f90f65a2","parentId":"db1cdc81","timestamp":"2026-04-14T06:14:57.447Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking me to evaluate two different SOPs for a TikTok Shop product selection process:\n\n1. **Their described flow (Feishu Bitable-centric)**: \n   - Paste TikTok product links into a Feishu Bitable\n   - Fields handle: title optimization, collect 1688 product selling points, TikTok product selling points\n   - 1688 product import, price calculation\n   - Main image generation, SKU image generation, series image generation\n   - Form a \"product premium\" (product listing)\n   - Export to a tool like \"店小秘\" (a Shopify/跨境电商 ERP)\n   - Each field can call different shortcuts/models to process data\n\n2. **The SOP they mentioned discussing yesterday**\n\nThe user cares about: efficiency and success rate.\n\nI should analyze both approaches, but first I should check memory for what was discussed yesterday about SOPs.\n\nLet me check memory files to understand the context of \"昨天的SOP\"."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_7vd03azqb7dt_1","name":"memory_search","arguments":{"query":"TikTok 选品 SOP 昨天"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776147284249,"responseId":"062d0e54ee696abdcd89329d49611362"}}
