{"type":"message","id":"0cf36758","parentId":"7ec89d64","timestamp":"2026-04-14T06:15:38.639Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"No memory results. Let me check today's memory file and also read the SOUL.md and TOOLS.md again to understand the current setup.\n\nHALEI is asking me to evaluate two SOPs:\n1. A Feishu Bitable-centric product selection flow (where you paste TikTok product links into a table, then use automation to fetch data, optimize titles, get 1688 product info, calculate prices, generate images, and export to an ERP tool like 店小秘)\n2. Our current SOP (from yesterday's discussion)\n\nHe cares about efficiency and success rate.\n\nLet me think about this:\n\n**The Feishu Bitable-centric approach he saw:**\n- Paste TikTok links into Bitable\n- Each field triggers automations (shortcuts/models) to:\n\n\n  - Collect 1688 product details (titles, selling points, pricing)\n  - Fetch TikTok product data\n  - Calculate profit margins\n  - Generate main images, SKU images, and other visuals\n  - Export everything to 店小秘 for publishing\n\n**Our current SOP (which I should recall from context):**\nBased on the SOUL.md and TOOLS.md, we have:\n- Daily data collection → initial screening → profit calculation → grade assessment\n- Output to Feishu Bitable (App Token: AKppbAeyXanToTsVl6ScxO5QnZd, Table ID: tblHU2do30jzinJT)\n- 9:00 data collection, 10\n\n:00 report output\n- Focus on Thailand and Vietnam markets, hair accessories category\n\nThe main differences are that their approach is manual link-pasting with more automation and image generation, while ours automates the entire data pipeline but lacks image generation. They also integrate with 店小秘 for publishing, whereas we haven't set that up yet.\n\nThe Bitable-centric approach would need strong automation for data fetching and image generation—there's real value in combining our structured data collection with their automated product research and image workflow."},{"type":"text","text":"这个问题挺实在的。让我先把咱们的现状和那个\"飞书表格为中心\"的方案做一个结构对比，效率的核心差异在于**哪个环节最费人工、最容易出错**。\n\n---\n\n## 两个SOP核心差异\n\n| 环节 | 咱们现有的 SOP | 那个\"飞书表格为中心\"的方案 |\n|------|--------------|--------------------------|\n| **数据采集** | Agent 自动采集 TikTok 热销榜/新品榜 | 手动粘贴 TikTok 链接 |\n| **1688 同款匹配** | 人工审核后录入链接 | 每个字段调用自动化/AI 匹配 |\n| **标题/卖点优化** | 暂无（输出表格后人工处理）| 字段自动化调用模型处理 |\n| **图片生成** | 暂无 | 主图/SKU图全自动生成 |\n| **价格/利润计算** | ✅ Agent 自动测算 | 字段公式自动计算 |\n| **ERP 上架** | 暂无 | 导出到店小秘 |\n| **人工介入点** | 审核推荐结果、确认采购 | 极少量，主要是粘贴链接 |\n\n---\n\n## 效率维度\n\n**那个方案的效率优势：**\n- 图片生成 + ERP 上架全自动，省掉美工和人工上传\n- 字段级自动化，出错后可以精准定位哪一步出了问题\n\n**咱们方案的优势：**\n- 采集和初筛全自动，不依赖\"看到某个品才处理\"\n- 选品逻辑（等级判定、IP过滤、硬性规则）Agent 帮你过滤，比纯手工粘贴可控性更强\n\n---\n\n## 我的判断：**两者结合最理想**\n\n咱们的 SOP 强在 **选品初筛 + 利润测算 + 等级判定** 这三步（数据驱动、可量化），但弱在\"后半段\"——1688 链接录入、图片、上架。\n\n**建议你考虑补充的流程：**\n1. **保留咱们现有的选品 SOP**（9:00 采集 → 利润测算 → 等级判定 → 推送到飞书表格）\n2. **在 Bitable 里加字段**：1688链接、图片生成状态、上架状态\n3. **后半段交给 Bitable 自动化**：链接粘贴 → 抓取1688卖点 → 图片生成 → 利润计算 → 导出店小秘\n\n也就是说：\n> **飞书表格是承接层 + 自动化中枢，而不是选品的起点。**\n\n起点还是咱们自动化的选品流程，表格负责后半段需要调用外部工具（图片、1688 API、ERP）的部分。\n\n---\n\n你觉得呢？现在主要卡在哪个环节——是选品命中率，还是后面的图片/上架？"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776147298175,"responseId":"062d0e625f1723a77401749ac057d291"}}
