{"type":"message","id":"0e71a1da","parentId":"fc2608ef","timestamp":"2026-04-14T06:25:54.489Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"System: [2026-04-14 14:25:52 GMT+8] Feishu[tts] DM | ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68 [msg:om_x100b52e99038b8a0c4dad8b95d73309]\n\nConversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b52e99038b8a0c4dad8b95d73309\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68\",\n  \"sender\": \"ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Tue 2026-04-14 14:25 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68\",\n  \"name\": \"ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68\"\n}\n```\n\n不是，我不是要导出到店小蜜，我觉得这流程我再说一下吧。你刚才描述的一个talkk里边的这个数据的这些数量资源呢，我们再调整，比如说30天之内，90天之内，7天之内，那首先呢，我们从他这儿呢，先去新品板拉取这个产品，拉取产品之后呢，筛选出有竞争力的，也不能去忽略它的竞争力，就我们实际是要对比一下，在1688上这个产品跟他现在的这个销售价中间的利润空间是多少。我们还要把当前市场上的这个整体的成本要都算进去。如果他OK成立，那我们就成，就怎么说，就成交，对吧，就是这个产品就可以采，是这样吗你说"}],"timestamp":1776147954487}}
{"type":"message","id":"ffde97b7","parentId":"0e71a1da","timestamp":"2026-04-14T06:26:30.278Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is clarifying their workflow. Let me understand what they're saying:\n\n1. They want to pull products from EchoTik's new product rankings\n2. Filter by different time windows (30 days, 90 days, 7 days)\n3. After pulling, filter for competitive products\n4. Calculate the profit margin by comparing:\n   - TikTok current selling price\n   - 1688 purchase cost (including all costs: product cost + shipping to China/warehouse + freight to Thailand/Vietnam)\n   - All market costs factored in\n5. If the math works out (profit margin meets requirements), then they proceed to source/purchase the product\n\nSo the key question is: **Is this the right approach?**\n\n\nThey've got it exactly right—this is the standard product selection framework. The core flow is straightforward: pull the product, assess whether it's worth sourcing by running the numbers on costs and potential profit margins, and if the numbers work, move forward with procurement."},{"type":"text","text":"对，你说的这个逻辑完全成立，而且这其实就是行业内标准的选品判断流程。\n\n---\n\n## 你的核心公式就这一句话：\n\n> **TikTok 售价 - (1688 采购成本 + 头程 + 平台抽成 + 退款预留) = 利润**\n>\n> **利润 ≥ 目标毛利率 → 可采**\n\n---\n\n## 具体路径是这样\n\n**① 从 EchoTik 拉新品榜**\n- 泰国站（TH）+ 越南站（VN）\n- 7天 / 30天 / 90天 三个时间窗口都拉，对比差异\n\n**② 筛选有竞争力的品**\n- 30天销量 100-300 单（起量初期）\n- 销量趋势上升（还没卷死）\n- 评分 ≥ 4.5（质量初步验证）\n\n**③ 算利润空间（最关键一步）**\n\n```\n以泰国站为例（越南类似）：\n\n1688 采购价假设 ¥8\n头程运费（假设100g）≈ ¥6\n平台抽成 ≈ 售价 × 15-20%\nTikTok 售价（EchoTik 里有）≈ THB 199\n\n套用你的公式：\nTHB 售价 = (¥8 + ¥6) × 5.0 × 1.25 ≈ THB 87.5 成本\n利润 = THB 199 - THB 87.5 = THB 111.5\n毛利率 = 56%  → 超过25%门槛 ✅ 可采\n```\n\n**④ 成交条件**\n- 毛利率 ≥ 25%（泰国）/ ≥ 20%（越南）\n- IP 风险无或低\n- 1688 同款能稳定供货\n\n---\n\n## 那你现在的 SOP 跟之前的区别是什么？\n\n| | 之前（数据驱动初筛）| 现在（利润闭环）|\n|---|---|---|\n| 核心判断 | 销量大、趋势好 | 利润空间够不够 |\n| 采购依据 | 有销量就能跟 | 算完账才决定 |\n| 风险点 | 可能跟了没利润 | 1688 同款匹配 |\n\n**你现在等于是在\"有动销信号\"的前提下，再加一道\"经济可行性\"门槛。**\n\n---\n\n所以这套逻辑是：**先看市场信号（EchoTik 数据），再算财务账（利润测算），最后决定采不采。**\n\n你觉得利润测算的参数（汇率、平台抽成比例、退款预留）有需要调整的吗？我可以帮你把公式固化到 Bitable 字段里。"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776147954489,"responseId":"062d10f2699ed2b09ab24b8cb57425df"}}
